sentences: Renate Spitzner (born 28 May 1943 in Prague, Czech Republic) is an Austrian composer (member of the "OeGZM" – Austrian Society of contemporary music), musician, music pedagogue, music therapist and founder of the "Music-social Method" – "Musisch-soziale Methode".
First time the "Music-social method" has been recognized and approved at the "United Nations Decade of Disabled Persons 1983–1992".
